title: Warehouse - custom font?
content:
Hello Typophiles,  
Trying to help a colleague track down a font calling itself “Warehouse”. Sample here: [http://jamesjohnston.net/warehouseScan.jpg](http://web.archive.org/web/20071126054903/http:/jamesjohnston.net/warehouseScan.jpg "http://jamesjohnston.net/warehouseScan.jpg")  
Is this a custom job?  
Regards  
PAUL

 [‹ Looking for 'Noise' font](http://web.archive.org/web/20071126054903/http:/www.typophile.com/node/27528 "Go to previous forum topic") [I found this on a sign ›](http://web.archive.org/web/20071126054903/http:/www.typophile.com/node/27539 "Go to next forum topic")
author: skyrocket

comments.content: Looks similarish to DIN or Fedra but not a match.

The only “Warehouse” I know of is from [House Industries](http://web.archive.org/web/20071126054903/http:/houseind.com/index.php?page=showfont&id=14&subpage=viewfonts).

- Lex
Thanks for the help Lex + David. Looks like a custom job then...
